    <div id="ftn36">&#13;
      <p><a href="#_ftnref36" name="_ftn36" id="_ftn36"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span>[36]</span></span></span></span></a><span> Mining&#13;&#13;
Lease Agreement Between Government of the Republic of Sierra Leone and African&#13;&#13;
Minerals Limited Group of Companies, Freetown, signed August 6, 2010. Mines and&#13;&#13;
Minerals Act 2009, <i>Sierra Leone Gazette</i>,&#13;&#13;
http://www.sierra-leone.org/Laws/2009-12.pdf. </span>In an independent&#13;&#13;
reconciliation report by the accounting firm Moore Stephens LLP concerning&#13;&#13;
revenue from Sierra Leone’s extractive industries in 2011, the firm found&#13;&#13;
that the multiple payments and inconsistent payment procedures undermined the “traceability&#13;&#13;
of the income flows paid by mining companies.” Sierra Leone Extractive&#13;&#13;
Industries Transparence Initiative, “Reconciliation Report for the Year&#13;&#13;
2011,” December 2013, p. 34. </p>&#13;
